HEADWORD: Contourn
<hw>Con`tour`n⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.,
p. p. of <ets>contourner</ets> to twist.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>Turned in a direction which is not the usual one; -- said of an
animal turned to the sinister which is usually turned to the dexter, or
the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contourniated</ent>⟦br⟧
